	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Dec 13th 6:33 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>i seem to be having some problems w/ too much weight for this race.&nbsp;&nbsp;this is my first character.  i am a wood elf ranger. i boosted my strength from 70 to 80 and my dexterity from 80 to 90.<br><br>i'm at lvl 10 now and have found that when i have my armor and a few bags, i cant hardly carry any loot home. when i set out my weight is about 65-70. so this leaves me w/ only 10-15 weight points left to bring home loot.  heck i've got so desperate i dont even carry my bow w/ me anymore.<br><br>right now i have a minotaur axe and a shield.  which both weigh a little more than a 2h sword.  but this is better damage.<br><br>any suggestions on what i can do?  do many wood elf ranger's have this prob?  do i just loot non-weapon items from now on?  or should i make a new character and give all 20 points to strength so he has 90 strength? if i could avoid that i would, as i've spend many hours alrady to get him to lvl 10.<br><br>any comments/suggestions/help would be appreciated. thx<br><br>Gilwen<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
