	   <tr><td colspan=2>I might be opposed by some with my opinion, but what you really want as wood elf ranger, is strength and ac. Get (if possible) some weight reducing bags. Later on you get a str spell, which helps. But...str adds to your attack, this is what you want, and ac ist the best friend you have. I personally think dexterity is not that much important as it helps with procing weapons, and some say how you hit with a bow. Stamina and agility are quite usefull, but agility above a certain level, does not give you too much ac, and does not help with dodge and reposte in an amazing brilliant way.<br><br>Spare some weight with the bags (backpack 3 small box 2) , it adds up.<br>If you can afford....leave rusty weapons, they don't sell for much and are VERY heavy. Get some jagged bands, they are great, give ac and str, and are not too expensive anymore. Don't look too much at the stats....what you want is ac, at least I notice this at level 50.<br>The beginning is hard concerning the weight....but belive me, for a ranger are still some very hard levels before you, when your defense skills stop , and go up only when you reach 51.<br>I have a wood elf too, and had the same troubles. But you have to go through it, till Str spell (lev 30) or till you can afford, or get weight reducing bags. You might be able to get lighter weapons, adn when you need to train dual wield or double attack, you won't use the shield anymore.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
