	   <tr><td colspan=2>as far as weight goes, i am not having much of a problem.&nbsp;&nbsp;how i did that is easy: look at the weight versus the ac, if you can afford some of the better armor.  if you lose an ac in order to save pounds in wieght, IMO you are doing good, as that loot won't slow you down if/when you have to run to zone.  this goes for armor, as well as weapons and a shield.  you might consider a silvery war axe for a weapon, as it is fairly light, and does decent dmg, with a low dly (6 and 22, if i remember right).  as far as bows/ archery, etc, hitting a mob with an arrow is a excellent way to get its attention.  try for a bow that has a balance between dly and dmg.  you can find bows that have a dly of 51, and ones that have a dly of as low as 39 (not counting the uzi).   the slower the bow, the higher the dmg, but only one shot. faster meaans less dmg, but chance for a second shot, usually.  fletching is excellent, even tho you have to dump a lot  of money into it to get very high quality arrows (as high as 8 dmg, 150 rng magic, i think) if you have the cash, do it.  also helps keep that down time for healing and medding from being boring.  but, this is just my opinion...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
