	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with the last on the bows and arrows.&nbsp;&nbsp;Start working on fletching skill.  Make arrows and then go use them, two birds, one stone.  Also, to make the trueshot longbow (dmg 20, dly 45, rg: 125) you need at a minimum 150 in fletching to make.  The quest items for a trueshot are easily gotten, but they are no drop so it is a real pain to get someone else to fletch it for you.  It is a great bow, and the items can be assembled by lvl 10 and up, so it is time and money well spent to boost fletching if only to make the trueshot.  It also sells for around 150pp, and u might spend 15 pp on materials, do the math.<br> <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
